example.p:
We know that in 5 hours the population will grow from 300 to 600. Therefore,

          300*b^{5}=600
          b^{5}=\frac{600}{300}
          b^{5}=2
          b=2^{\frac{1}{5}}
          b \approx 1.1487

        so our formula is P(t) \approx 300(1.1487)^{t}

